Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.39,0:00:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enjoy yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.15,0:00:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.15,0:00:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.53,0:00:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you said "tea," I didn't\Nthink you actually meant "tea."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.16,0:00:17.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Relax. I'm picking up the tab.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.53,0:00:18.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.45,0:00:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nakajo didn't pan out?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.71,0:00:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nor Haba?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.08,0:00:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.00,0:00:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nor Sawakiguchi, either?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.59,0:00:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.38,0:00:35.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.18,0:00:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to say it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.59,0:00:38.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to worry about being polite.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.02,0:00:45.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would like you to tell me, then,\Nwhat about them was so wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.27,0:00:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, let's start with\NNakajo-{\i1}senpai{\i0}'s theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.94,0:00:59.37,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I scowled at the wind blowing\Nat my window of boredom{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.37,0:01:07.42,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}so I could turn away\Nthe awkwardness I was feeling{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.75,0:01:15.59,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.59,0:01:21.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I nod noncommittally at today\Nas I hold it in my hand{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.01,0:01:26.39,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}projecting myself a little exaggeratedly{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.39,0:01:31.90,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I get the feeling that\Nsomething is about to change{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.90,0:01:36.99,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's all because of you\Ncalling out to my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.41,0:01:43.83,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Peeking up at cloudy skies,\NI sense what's coming{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.83,0:01:51.84,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's reach out our hands\Nwith courage stronger than ever{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.25,0:01:56.84,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Light and shadow are both still far off{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.84,0:02:03.10,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but even so, we want to know\Nthe reason for this kindness{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.10,0:02:10.52,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's go look now, beyond the brilliance\Nthat goes by nobody's name{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.52,0:02:18.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}before it all becomes a thing of the past{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.99,0:02:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tea Room Hifumi
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.95,0:02:27.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which is why I couldn't adopt\NSawakiguchi-{\i1}senpai{\i0}'s idea, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.91,0:02:28.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.75,0:02:33.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Blind Spot to All
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.92,0:02:34.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was it that turned down Nakajo's idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.63,0:02:36.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.38,0:02:38.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And was it the same for\NHaba and Sawakiguchi?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.01,0:02:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.51,0:02:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I first asked you\Nto solve this problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.51,0:02:46.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you said you didn't want\Nme to expect too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.89,0:02:50.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then you went and put to rest\Nevery last one of their ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.60,0:02:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I secretly thought you would.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.27,0:02:54.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You thought I would?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.86,0:02:57.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It turns out that they weren't\Nup to the challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.07,0:03:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew from the start that they didn't have\Nthe necessary skill to solve this problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.36,0:03:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was just a charade? Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.24,0:03:07.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I'm not saying\Nthat they are incapable.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.12,0:03:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They possess skill that\Nis hard to come by.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.70,0:03:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even so, that doesn't make\Nthem of any use in this situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.21,0:03:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did...\NIf you weren't...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.38,0:03:20.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you weren't around, we would\Nhave used one of their ideas,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.76,0:03:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the production would likely\Nhave ended up a failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.05,0:03:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's pretty cold. Not to mention cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.64,0:03:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we must, that's what we'll do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.68,0:03:32.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there is one other person\Nthat we can turn to.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.02,0:03:37.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have heard from three different\Npeople about this person's ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.73,0:03:41.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One is Chitanda Eru. One is\Nsomeone outside the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.11,0:03:43.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The last one is Togaito Masashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.78,0:03:47.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This person might be able to\Nserve as the video's detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.24,0:03:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.50,0:03:52.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was after {\i1}you {\i0}from the beginning,\Nnot the Classic Lit Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.67,0:03:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.38,0:04:03.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Given all that has happened, I consider\Nyou to have proven your skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.26,0:04:05.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.34,0:04:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are special.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.69,0:04:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are special.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.53,0:04:21.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I would like to ask you one more time...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.78,0:04:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}kun{\i0}, please, help out Class 2-F.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.95,0:04:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you to find a\Nsolution to this video.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.87,0:04:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any skills.\NI just happened to get lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.42,0:04:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How disappointing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.33,0:04:41.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then allow me to say something else.\NConsider it an amusing anecdote.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.09,0:04:43.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A certain athletic club had a benchwarmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.14,0:04:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The benchwarmer tried extremely\Nhard to become a regular,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.10,0:04:51.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but she just couldn't make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.10,0:04:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was because the club had other, far\Nmore capable members than the benchwarmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.48,0:05:01.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Among them was someone who\Nwas born with natural ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.23,0:05:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her talent was, of course, the difference between\Nnight and day when compared to the benchwarmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.82,0:05:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At one competition, she\Nperformed extremely well,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.66,0:05:11.41,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Prize
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.45,0:05:11.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and was even chosen as the MVP.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.41,0:05:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An interviewer asked her,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.04,0:05:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"That was quite a feat.\NWhat is your secret?"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.25,0:05:19.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She answered him,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.67,0:05:22.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I just happened to get lucky."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.30,0:05:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that her answer sounded\Nfairly caustic to the benchwarmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.01,0:05:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.89,0:05:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone ought to recognize who they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.77,0:05:40.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, it makes fools\Nof those watching them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.48,0:05:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I special?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.40,0:05:51.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do I truly give myself enough\Ncredit for who I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.04,0:05:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it right for me to believe it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.76,0:06:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Irisu-{\i1}senpai{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.47,0:06:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.76,0:06:16.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is unusual... you going to the school\Non your own during vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.48,0:06:18.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have some business there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.73,0:06:22.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I not go to school without\Nhaving any business there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.06,0:06:24.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it just goes against the grain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.98,0:06:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I received a personal\Nrequest from Irisu-{\i1}senpai{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.57,0:06:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to identify the\Nculprit that killed Kaito.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.70,0:06:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah? No kidding. {\i1}You{\i0}, Hotaro?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.66,0:06:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki Hotaro is both dutiful and devoted.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.95,0:06:37.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure I heard that. One more time?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.62,0:06:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.50,0:06:42.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, this is quite a\Nchange of heart, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.33,0:06:44.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was Chitanda-{\i1}san {\i0}the reason\Nbehind it this time, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.34,0:06:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.25,0:06:47.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, what {\i1}was {\i0}the reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.26,0:06:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If I don't have to do\Nsomething, I don't do it."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.68,0:06:51.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's your motto, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.76,0:06:55.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.22,0:06:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.90,0:07:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think that there's anything\Nthat only you can accomplish?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.24,0:07:09.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.57,0:07:11.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.66,0:07:14.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't I told you? I\Ndon't have any talents.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.28,0:07:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For example, I fancy myself a Sherlockian.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.83,0:07:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I could never be one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.00,0:07:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I lack the basic nerve necessary\Nto forge my way headlong
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.42,0:07:28.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,into the deep and rarefied\Nlabyrinth of knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.59,0:07:33.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Mayaka were to turn her interest\Ntoward Holmes, I guarantee you,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.39,0:07:36.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she'd pass me up in three months.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.51,0:07:40.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I go around peeking into the\Ndoorways of various genres,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.31,0:07:44.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and getting my pamphlet stamped.\NThat's the most that I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.73,0:07:46.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't ever be an\Nauthority on anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.36,0:07:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it. Irisu-{\i1}senpai {\i0}roped you into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.28,0:07:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nonetheless, you're still having\Nmisgivings about your own aptitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.49,0:08:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you never have doubts about yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.62,0:08:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really. I'm going on ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.42,0:08:07.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka should already be at school,\Nso I'm going to say hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.29,0:08:08.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.75,0:08:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.42,0:08:14.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure what you think,\Nbut I give you more value than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.84,0:08:17.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you wanted to, someday,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.22,0:08:20.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you could be one of the\Nfinest Sherlockians in all of Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.44,0:08:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are any number of things\Nthat are more appealing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.90,0:08:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,than being a Sherlockian.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.73,0:08:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though I have to admit...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.53,0:08:33.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't be more envious,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.70,0:08:35.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.04,0:08:41.95,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Science Prep Room
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.04,0:08:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's summer vacation, and Oreki\Nvoluntarily came to school?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.96,0:08:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something wrong with me being here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.50,0:08:48.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's wrong, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.67,0:08:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's creepy, like the prelude\Nto an apocalyptic disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.88,0:08:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I decided to help solve the mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.59,0:08:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.14,0:09:01.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aha! I'll bet Irisu-{\i1}senpai {\i0}seduced\Nyou with something, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.02,0:09:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka, you're sharp, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.60,0:09:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, whatever. Never mind me,\Nhow did it go after you left yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.65,0:09:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}? She seemed\Nto get home all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.19,0:09:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I called her this morning, and she\Nwas sick in bed with a hangover.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.49,0:09:19.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now {\i1}that's {\i0}a rare case, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.58,0:09:24.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahem. Well, anyway,\Nlet's watch that movie again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.46,0:09:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.30,0:09:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I-It's blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.05,0:09:42.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.52,0:09:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito-{\i1}senpai{\i0}'s arm there\Nreally is nicely done.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.98,0:09:49.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks just like a real arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.69,0:09:53.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The prop makers might be the most\Ncapable ones of all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.90,0:09:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.87,0:10:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It sure doesn't {\i1}look {\i0}like\Nthere's a fancy setup, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.29,0:10:06.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Something so difficult\Nis being made to look simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.79,0:10:08.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No it's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.58,0:10:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason it looks simple isn't because\Nit was set up to look that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.29,0:10:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.34,0:10:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's what I think. This video\Njust makes for a dull movie,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.51,0:10:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and it has no appeal to the viewer,\Nwhich is why the mystery doesn't pop.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.76,0:10:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ho...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.31,0:10:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The volunteers of Class 2-F,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.18,0:10:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,having decided to participate\Nin the Kanyasai...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.98,0:10:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true. Seeing it for the first time,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.81,0:10:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't even realize that it was\Na locked-room murder movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.77,0:10:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The production is awfully weak, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.57,0:10:37.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such as?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.74,0:10:39.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The camerawork is poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.70,0:10:40.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, there's that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.91,0:10:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then Ibara, how would you shoot it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.24,0:10:46.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it were me? Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.87,0:10:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For example, let's see here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.50,0:10:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.92,0:10:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't it be more effective\Nto shoot this from farther away,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.00,0:10:57.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to show the characters together\Nwith the room's interior?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.30,0:10:59.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.51,0:11:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.22,0:11:01.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.89,0:11:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Sugimura! How about you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.97,0:11:08.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's fairly clean in here.\NWe might be able to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.43,0:11:11.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it would be better to shoot\Nthis from Sugimura-{\i1}senpai{\i0}'s view
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.31,0:11:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to make it easier to tell that the lobby\Nis in full view from up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.07,0:11:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the camera looks up\Nat him from the lobby,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.11,0:11:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that point doesn't get conveyed\Nto the viewer, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.40,0:11:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see, what else...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.24,0:11:24.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but that's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.16,0:11:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.33,0:11:26.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll go on forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.49,0:11:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.37,0:11:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Criticizing how bad the video is\Nwon't get us anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.37,0:11:33.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, it might be good\Nto study it a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.88,0:11:36.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found you, Fukube!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.59,0:11:40.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So {\i1}this {\i0}is where you've\Nbeen goofing around!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.30,0:11:41.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Yamauchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}, welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.30,0:11:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, no need to get violent!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.93,0:11:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm doing this for your own good!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.85,0:11:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have lots of other things to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.73,0:11:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot! Omichi isn't messing around!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.06,0:11:55.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you care if you fail\Nto pass the class?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.11,0:11:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi, you should go take\Nthose remedial lessons.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.86,0:12:01.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But Hongo-{\i1}senpai{\i0}'s mystery\Nis important, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.65,0:12:04.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro, go ahead and pull the solution\Nout of thin air right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.37,0:12:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of nonsense\Nare you going on about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.66,0:12:08.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.08,0:12:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I want to know the secret! The secret!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.46,0:12:15.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.67,0:12:17.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is he, an idiot?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.17,0:12:19.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.59,0:12:23.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Hotaro. The constraints\Nof the world are beyond my control.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.93,0:12:25.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Having come to this...\NFukube!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.35,0:12:28.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think of this notebook as being me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.76,0:12:30.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.06,0:12:32.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! I'm coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.69,0:12:33.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For Pete's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.73,0:12:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, I have to go, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.61,0:12:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.19,0:12:39.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you looking at me like that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.86,0:12:44.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Irisu-{\i1}senpai {\i0}may be one thing,\Nbut I am {\i1}not {\i0}planning to help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.36,0:12:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'Zat so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.24,0:12:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have library duty. If I had\Nknown we'd be doing this,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.66,0:12:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would have left my schedule\Nopen ahead of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.37,0:12:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's your own fault for\Nspringing this on us. Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.71,0:12:58.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Oreki.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.43,0:13:08.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay then...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.60,0:13:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's split up and look around inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.43,0:13:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.98,0:13:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! Who did this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.10,0:13:17.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I-It's blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.65,0:13:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay. I'm sure there are keys.\NEh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.09,0:13:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.59,0:13:49.18,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,No unauthorized personnel
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.55,0:13:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.35,0:13:53.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is what Hongo intended.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.97,0:13:56.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shosho {\i0}('Heat's End')\NFor the sunshine easeth,\Nand blue skies begin their withdrawl
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.27,0:13:56.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.02,0:14:01.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.57,0:14:07.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, I'd like to ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.82,0:14:09.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,did you reach a conclusion?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.58,0:14:13.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay then, let's hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.45,0:14:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.50,0:14:17.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It goes without saying
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.46,0:14:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the locked room is\Nthe key to this mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.71,0:14:23.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The room that Kaito...\NI mean, Kaito-{\i1}senpai {\i0}died in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.42,0:14:25.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,could not have been entered\Nby any of the other members,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.88,0:14:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nor could they leave it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.68,0:14:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can forgo the "{\i1}senpai{\i0}."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.85,0:14:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stage left wing is a locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.56,0:14:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! Who did this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.35,0:14:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only other exit, this window,\Nwas in the condition you see here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.36,0:14:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which makes it inconceivable that the killer\Ncame or left by any means except for the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.90,0:14:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So how did they do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.45,0:14:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's unclear from the video whether\Nor not the door is rigged.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.24,0:14:54.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means it's most reasonable to assume
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.54,0:14:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the killer used the\Nmaster key to let themselves in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.58,0:15:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the lobby was under\NSugimura's observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.71,0:15:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a result, the killer couldn't have\Neven entered the right hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.80,0:15:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This creates a second locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.30,0:15:11.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,None of our six characters could have gotten\Nthe master key from out of the office,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.84,0:15:13.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then gone down the right hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.97,0:15:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what does that leave us with?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.39,0:15:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If none of the six are the killer,\Nthere can be only one conclusion...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.35,0:15:23.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a seventh character there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.86,0:15:26.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A seventh character?\NLike Sawakiguchi was saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.57,0:15:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. When she first came up with it,\NI thought it was pretty absurd,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.03,0:15:33.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but according to Sawakiguchi,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.78,0:15:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hongo was looking for someone\Nto play a seventh character.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.41,0:15:40.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remembering that, I became convinced.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.50,0:15:44.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, Hongo wrote the script\Nto play it straight with the viewer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.79,0:15:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's unimaginable that a phantom\Ncharacter would suddenly appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.13,0:15:52.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally, there were a number\Nof odd occurrences in the video.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.43,0:15:54.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satoshi wrote about these.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.85,0:15:59.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Konosu finds the floorplan.\NIt is illuminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.39,0:16:01.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe it to be a flashlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.77,0:16:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another spot, when they\Ngo searching for Kaito.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.52,0:16:09.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hall is dark. Not enough light.\NA flashlight is used."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.28,0:16:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A flashlight, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.86,0:16:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.11,0:16:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And none of the featured characters\Nare carrying a flashlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.33,0:16:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looking at the scene right after\Nwhere the flashlight is shown,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.20,0:16:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,such as immediately following\Ntheir entry into the crime scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.67,0:16:24.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this can clearly be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.46,0:16:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was enough time\Nto hide the flashlight,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.88,0:16:30.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but there isn't any\Nlegitimate reason to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.01,0:16:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, you want to say that\Nit's simply scene lighting, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.47,0:16:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But please, keep this in mind for later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.72,0:16:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's another thing... and please don't take\Noffense, as this is coming from a film lover.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.56,0:16:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"This movie is dull. It\Nwas poorly produced.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.15,0:16:48.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The camerawork in particular\Nhad no innovation at all."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.40,0:16:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what if there was a reason for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.24,0:16:58.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This movie was shot with the cameraman\Nalways in the same place as the other six.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.83,0:17:01.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you might have\Nfigured it out by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.50,0:17:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.50,0:17:08.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the cameraman is\Nthe seventh character?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.38,0:17:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were seven of them from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.38,0:17:18.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The six of them in the picture,\Nand the cameraman shooting them,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.05,0:17:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for a total of seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.30,0:17:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please watch closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.35,0:17:24.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are some scenes where the\Nactors pay attention to the camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.35,0:17:28.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were aware that the\Ncameraman was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.86,0:17:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calling him the cameraman is misleading.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.53,0:17:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about we call him the seventh man?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.61,0:17:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As for the flashlight illumination,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.90,0:17:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it wouldn't be out of place to\Nthink that he was carrying one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.41,0:17:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The poor quality of the camerawork,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.87,0:17:44.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the fact that he couldn't shoot the scene\Nfrom multiple angles at the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.66,0:17:47.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,becomes more convincing if you\Nthink of him as a character.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.83,0:17:50.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also... and this is important...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.88,0:17:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the others departed\Nthe interior of the scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.51,0:17:56.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the camera was still in the lobby\Nafter everyone was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.43,0:17:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The scene then fades out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.72,0:18:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, after the\Ncamera stops temporarily,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.06,0:18:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it was waiting there in the lobby\Nfor the others to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.14,0:18:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As such, the crime is simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.56,0:18:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The seventh character waited for\Nthe others to leave the stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.07,0:18:14.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and after stopping the\Ncamera he was holding,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.78,0:18:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he moved quickly to obtain\Nthe master key from the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.53,0:18:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After killing Kaito, he uses it\Nto lock up the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.20,0:18:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then he waited in the lobby\Nfor the others to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.42,0:18:30.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is my conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.63,0:18:34.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Hongo had not chosen\Na seventh actor yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.17,0:18:37.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I recommend that you find one\Nas soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.80,0:18:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two things...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.18,0:18:41.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, if that were true,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.30,0:18:43.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the fact that the seventh\Nperson never says anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.22,0:18:46.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nor does anyone ever speak to him,\Ncomes off as awkward, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.43,0:18:48.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hongo may have been\Nusing that as a motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.52,0:18:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The seventh character was one\Nthat the other six ignored.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.94,0:18:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a result, he was unable\Nto speak up, himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.44,0:19:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Second, if that were true,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.07,0:19:04.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the characters in the movie would reach\Nthe same conclusion before long.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.16,0:19:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They would all suspect the seventh man,\Nwho remained in the lobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.54,0:19:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, the "second locked room"\Nthat you speak of is still intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.46,0:19:15.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can assume that the seventh man's\Nmovements were in public view.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.92,0:19:19.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In which case, they would know\Nwho the culprit was right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.88,0:19:23.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I may borrow an expression\Nfrom Sawakiguchi,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.60,0:19:25.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"What does it really matter?"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.02,0:19:30.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who really cares if the cast\Nof characters know who it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.27,0:19:33.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as the viewers are puzzled\Nby the mystery, isn't that enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.44,0:19:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That may be why there's no\Ndetective character in the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.32,0:19:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need for the folks in\Nthe show to reach a deduction
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.36,0:19:42.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because it's obvious to\Nthem who the killer is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.50,0:19:57.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.50,0:19:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.42,0:20:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like you solved Hongo's mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.76,0:20:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a surprisingly bold\Napproach, to be sure,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.89,0:20:08.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but since it corresponds\Nto all of the facts,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.14,0:20:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there can be no doubt that you are right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.60,0:20:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.77,0:20:15.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we can finish the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.24,0:20:24.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like my estimation\Nof you was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.20,0:20:26.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You do have the skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.08,0:20:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A power that no one else has.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.24,0:20:33.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Er, well, I'm... most grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.46,0:20:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about it? Would you like to be\Nthe one to give the movie a title?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.30,0:20:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A title?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.34,0:20:40.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just off the top of your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.92,0:20:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as you're the one who thinks of it,\NI'm sure everyone will approve.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.93,0:20:45.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.76,0:20:51.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's see... in keeping\Nwith the content...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.85,0:20:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think about\N"Blind Spot to All"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.44,0:20:57.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.82,0:21:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good title. Let's settle on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.87,0:21:13.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Home run.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.83,0:21:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.58,0:21:19.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For all of you 3rd-years...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.71,0:21:22.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,October brings with it\Nthe culture festival...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.60,0:21:35.48,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a screening of the movie in the\NAV room. We are already there.... Chitanda
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.48,0:21:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just don't think anyone could\Nhave gotten near that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.65,0:21:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true. With the exception\Nof one person... you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.49,0:21:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.03,0:21:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who did this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.45,0:21:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.20,0:21:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you do something like this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.37,0:21:50.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?!\NSurprised, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.95,0:21:52.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.16,0:21:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you running away?!\NGive yourself up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.83,0:21:57.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He pulled it off, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.92,0:21:59.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, that really was a great ending!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.92,0:22:01.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the real Kaito.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.92,0:22:01.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, really. Who'd\Nhave guessed it was the cameraman?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.59,0:22:03.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I heard!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.42,0:22:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It turns out that you're the one\Nwho thought this up, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.72,0:22:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.30,0:22:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, that was a surprise ending!\NNo complaints!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.22,0:22:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! It's the great detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.56,0:22:17.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.10,0:22:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Way to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.06,0:22:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although, it's too bad that when\Nthe seventh character is revealed,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.32,0:22:25.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they turn violent, and all gang up on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.69,0:22:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.61,0:22:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, anyhow, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.74,0:22:29.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.99,0:22:31.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.49,0:22:32.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Nakajo...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.99,0:22:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.62,0:22:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your pit sweat is out of control.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.29,0:22:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll never get a girl that way. That arm\Nwas worth all the work we put into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.96,0:22:38.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tch!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.71,0:22:41.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like it wasn't to Haba's liking.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.84,0:22:43.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.13,0:22:44.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.13,0:22:45.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, now let's submit\Nit to the executive committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.55,0:22:45.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.55,0:22:46.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm, not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.84,0:22:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was interesting. Who'd have\Nguessed the cameraman did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.10,0:22:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Had you thought about this last time?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.52,0:22:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, at the time, I hadn't come up with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.02,0:22:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.81,0:23:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? She doesn't seem very surprised.\NThat's our Hotaro for you, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.31,0:23:03.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right. I hate to admit it, though.\NWell, what do I expect?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.65,0:23:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.03,0:23:05.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.90,0:23:07.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.86,0:23:12.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... I'll tell you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.25,0:23:18.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, anyhow, well done, Hotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.62,0:23:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The "Empress" is satisfied,\Nand the movie is finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.46,0:23:24.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The viewers will enjoy the\Nelement of surprise, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.88,0:23:28.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.84,0:23:31.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I have to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.43,0:23:32.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.93,0:23:34.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, come on...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.81,0:23:37.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki, you're the one who came up\Nwith that solution, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.52,0:23:38.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.52,0:23:38.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.93,0:23:39.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mostly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.19,0:23:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what do you think about\Nwhat Haba-{\i1}senpai {\i0}said?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.69,0:23:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haba?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.78,0:23:48.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.03,0:23:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't use the rope\Nanywhere in that movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.58,0:23:58.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.04,0:24:07.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.96,0:24:11.72,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.72,0:24:15.72,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.72,0:24:21.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.20,0:24:41.29,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The heat of your budding warmth troubles me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.04,0:24:52.05,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't you understand how I feel yet?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.47,0:24:58.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There isn't supposed to be\Nany significance in your glance{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.97,0:25:04.35,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I mean, it's the same one\Nyou give all your friends{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.35,0:25:10.07,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The tiny wishing star fading\Ninto the morning light{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.07,0:25:15.07,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and the magic it works during the night\N(I wish you would notice){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.07,0:25:18.12,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.12,0:25:21.83,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.83,0:25:25.87,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.87,0:25:31.09,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.68,0:25:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Credit Roll of Fools."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.14,0:25:43.52,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Credit Roll of Fools
